A protein that contains a copy of the 'Paired box' domain (Pfam:PF00292), a conserved amino acid motif with DNA-binding activity. Members of this class are transcription factors involved in pattern formation during embryogenesis, possibly by determining the time and place of organ initiation or morphogenesis.
